SUMMARY:The Many Lives of Dance
DESCRIPTION:A movement practice is inherently living\, breathing\, and evolving. \nDance is many things at once. A rigorous system of knowledge\, shaped by centuries of technique\, philosophy\, and discipline. A language moving through communities\, carried by rhythm\, presence\, and collective energy. A deeply personal practice\, uniquely created by each mind\, body and soul.  \nThe Many Lives of Dance is an eight day long series in honour of World Dance Day\, bringing together artists\, scholars\, and practitioners across forms\, traditions\, and contexts. From ancient rhythms to modern beats\, the codified to the improvised\, the performed to the participatory.\n \nPlease note: There is no event on Apr 28 \n\n\n\nDate\nEvent\nArtist\nNature\nTiming\n\n\nApr 26\nPerspectives on Bharatanatyam\nLeela Samson and Bhavajan Kumar\nLecture Demonstration\n11:30am – 1pm\n\n\nApr 26\nSole to Soul\nJanani Kalasutra\nWorkshop\n4pm – 6pm\n\n\nApr 27\nDāri | The Path\nAvijit Das\, Varsha\, Greeshma and Abhirami\nPerformance\n7pm – 8:30pm\n\n\nApr 29\nWhat Holds\nGayatri Shetty\nPerformance\n7pm – 8:15pm\n\n\nApr 30\nMaṇṇina Hejje –  Dances of the Soil\nSneha Kappanna\nWorkshop\n6:30pm – 8:30pm\n\n\nMay 1\nIlluminating Dance\nNiranjan Gokhale\nLecture Demonstration\n2pm – 4pm\n\n\nMay 1\nWhy Dance When No One is Watching?\nDiya Naidu\nLecture Demonstration\n6:30pm – 8:30pm\n\n\nMay 2\nBody as Resource\nPreethi Rajagopalan\nWorkshop\n3pm – 5pm\n\n\nMay 3\nGabbu Kathe\nKeerthi Kumar and Roopa Krishnamurthy\nPerformance\n11:30am – 12:30pm\n\n\nMay 3\nThehraav\nMasoom Parmar\nTalk\n5pm – 6:30pm\n\n\n\n  \n
URL:https://bangaloreinternationalcentre.org/event/the-many-lives-of-dance/
LOCATION:Bangalore International Centre\, 7\, 4th Main Road\, Domlur II Stage\, Bangalore\, Karnataka\, 560071\, India
CATEGORIES:Dance,Performing Arts
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://bangaloreinternationalcentre.org/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Thumbnail_TMLOD2.jpg
