SUMMARY:Gabbu Kathe
DESCRIPTION:Language: English \nGabbu\, the Garbage King\, was born from human neglect and forgotten waste. One day\, a sharp and curious ragpicker finds him. This dance-drama is the playful and imaginative encounter between them. \nThrough Kathak\, contemporary movement\, mime\, humour and multimedia elements\, this performance unfolds as a vibrant fantasy world where discarded objects hold memories and stories of their own. What begins as a chance meeting grows into a journey of discovery\, and shared responsibility. \nBalancing satire with tenderness\, Gabbu Kathe invites children and families to reflect on their relationship with waste\, care\, and the environment. At the end of the performance\, children will be taught a short section of the choreography they witnessed.  \nWaste is not the end of a cycle\, but rather the beginning of a conversation around renewal\, empathy and collective action.  \nCredits:\nConcept\, Script\, Design & Direction: Keerthi Kumar & Roopa Krishnamurthy\nOriginal music score: Praveen D Rao & Sagar Gururaj\nArtwork: Rohit Bhasi\nPerformed: Roopa\, Keerthi Kumar\, Bharat Rajan\, Ashwin\nChoreographic Supervision & Lighting Design: Yonitha Jain\nCommissioned by Alif Arts as part of BLR Hubba\nProduced by ARTMOS \n\nThis event is a part of our programming to celebrate World Dance Day 2026\, ‘The Many Lives of Dance’. \n\n\nSupported by:\n\n
URL:https://bangaloreinternationalcentre.org/event/gabbu-kathe/
LOCATION:Bangalore International Centre\, 7\, 4th Main Road\, Domlur II Stage\, Bangalore\, Karnataka\, 560071\, India
CATEGORIES:Dance,Performing Arts,Theatre,Young BIC
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://bangaloreinternationalcentre.org/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Thumbnail-6.jpg
END:VEVENT
