UID:88569-1777824000-1777829400@bangaloreinternationalcentre.org
SUMMARY:A Search for the Magical Everything
DESCRIPTION:The paper you write on was once a tree.  \nThe tree was once a seed.  \nThe seed was once… well\, that is exactly the kind of question Ila asks. \nThe Magical Everything by Jenny Pinto is a hybrid graphic novel for middle and high school readers\, beautifully illustrated by Sharon Dev. Through Ila’s adventures across evolutionary history\, it traces the deep interconnections of life on Earth and asks how we arrived at the crisis we find ourselves in today. \nJenny Pinto will read a section of her book. After that\, you will need to roll up your sleeves. In a hands-on paper-making activity\, we will discover what regeneration really means. How nature takes everything back and begins again\, and why some things\, like plastic\, disrupt this cycle. \nPlease note: This session is designed for children accompanied by one adult. Come ready to get a little wet\, as this hands-on paper-making session can get delightfully messy! \nAround the World in 50 Sundays is a journey that begins\, not with a ticket\, but with opening a book. In a city like Bangalore where families are always in motion\, the BIC Library hopes to offer stillness and a quiet\, welcoming space for both parents and children where reading becomes a shared way of being and not a task. \nEvery Sunday\, we open our doors to invite you into a library that listens; building a rhythm of return\, a habit of joy and a new community bound not just by books\, but by the weekly ritual of reading together. \nWe welcome your ideas and input. If you have suggestions for children’s events or activities that align with this vision\, we’d love to hear from you. Please reach out to us at library@bangaloreinternationalcentre.org \nSupported by:\n \n
URL:https://bangaloreinternationalcentre.org/event/a-search-for-the-magical-everything/
LOCATION:Bangalore International Centre\, 7\, 4th Main Road\, Domlur II Stage\, Bangalore\, Karnataka\, 560071\, India
CATEGORIES:Around the World in 50 Sundays,Children's Books,Climate Change,Sustainability
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://bangaloreinternationalcentre.org/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Thumbnail-44.jpg
END:VEVENT
